title Gender as a Cultural Construct (March 2022)
style wardley

// Anchor: the individual person whose gender is lived, expressed, constructed
anchor Individual [0.97, 0.40]

// Lived & expressed layer (individual / emergent cluster)
component Identity [0.88, 0.55]
component Lived Experience [0.82, 0.32]
component Self-Expression [0.80, 0.50]
component Gender Expression [0.72, 0.55]
component Gender Identity [0.68, 0.42]
component Sexual Identity [0.64, 0.57]
component Sexual Orientation [0.55, 0.65]

// Embodied substrate bridge
component Phenotype [0.50, 0.82]

// Cultural codification layer: memory, stories, symbols codify roles
component Memory Stories Symbols [0.48, 0.72] inertia

// Values and beliefs carried by collectives
component Values Rights Beliefs [0.40, 0.63]

// Collective structures (industrialised social machinery)
component Family [0.38, 0.86]
component Institutions [0.28, 0.93]

// Power hierarchies (asymmetry: Patriarchy dominant, Matriarchy rare)
component Matriarchy [0.25, 0.28]
component Patriarchy [0.18, 0.92] inertia

// Structural machinery of exclusion / concentration
component Class Property Ownership [0.10, 0.90]

// Biological substrate (genetic markers, epigenetics, environment)
component Biological Substrate [0.08, 0.75]

// Dependencies (a -> b means a depends on b)
Individual->Identity
Individual->Lived Experience
Individual->Self-Expression
Identity->Gender Identity
Identity->Sexual Identity
Identity->Gender Expression
Lived Experience->Gender Expression
Lived Experience->Memory Stories Symbols
Self-Expression->Gender Expression
Gender Expression->Gender Identity
Gender Identity->Sexual Orientation
Sexual Identity->Sexual Orientation
Gender Expression->Phenotype
Gender Identity->Phenotype
Sexual Orientation->Phenotype
Phenotype->Biological Substrate
Memory Stories Symbols->Values Rights Beliefs
Values Rights Beliefs->Family
Values Rights Beliefs->Institutions
Family->Patriarchy
Family->Matriarchy
Institutions->Patriarchy
Patriarchy->Class Property Ownership
Matriarchy->Class Property Ownership
Patriarchy->Biological Substrate

// Predicted 12-24 month evolution (from March 2022)
evolve Gender Identity 0.55
evolve Lived Experience 0.45

// Strategic annotations
annotation 1 [[0.18, 0.92]] Power concentrates here: Patriarchy is Commodity-stage, ubiquitous, invisible, high inertia
annotation 2 [[0.82, 0.32]] Individual & emergent zone (top-left): bespoke per person, actively evolving
annotation 3 [[0.25, 0.28]] Matriarchy: Custom-Built, rare; the asymmetry is the power story
annotation 4 [[0.68, 0.42]] Active frontier: contested and rapidly hardening into Product stage
